{{Infobox language |name=Guro |altname=Kweni |region=[[Ivory Coast]] |speakers=500,000 |date=2012 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam1=[[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] |fam2=[[Mande languages|Mande]] |fam3=Eastern Mande |fam4=Southeastern |fam5=Mano–Dan |fam6=Guro–Tura |fam7=Guro–Yaure |iso3=goa |glotto=guro1248 |glottorefname=Guro }}
'''Guro''' (Gouro), also known as '''Kweni''' (Kwéndré) and Lo, is a [[Mande language]] spoken by approximately a million people in [[Ivory Coast]], primarily in the areas of [[Haut-Sassandra]] and [[Marahoue]], and the Goh.
