{{Infobox language |name=Kpala |states=[[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[Republic of Congo]] |region=[[Province of Équateur|Équateur]] Province (NW) |speakers={{sigfig|18,600|2}} |date=1986–1993 |ref = e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam1=[[Ubangian languages|Ubangian]] |fam2=Sere–Mba |fam3=[[Ngbaka languages|Ngbaka]] |fam4=Western |lc1=moj|ld1=Monzombo |lc2=kpl|ld2=Kpala |lc3=yng|ld3=Yango |glotto=monz1253 |glottorefname=Monzomboic }}
'''Monzombo''' is a minor [[Ubangian language]] of the Congos.
There are three varieties, Monzombo (Mondjembo), Kpala (Kwala), and Yango, which ''Ethnologue'' lists separately. It is not clear how distinct they are.
