{{Infobox language |name=Muher |region=Ethiopia |speakers=90,000 |date=no date |ref=<ref>{{e15|sgw|Sebat Bet Gurage}}</ref> |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Semitic languages|Semitic]] |fam3=[[South Semitic languages|South Semitic]] |fam4=[[Ethiopian Semitic languages|Ethiopian Semitic]] |fam5=[[West Gurage languages|West Gurage]] |iso3=none |glotto=none |linglist=sgw-muh }} '''Muher''' (''Muxar'') is an [[Ethiopian Semitic languages|Ethiopian Semitic language]] belonging to the [[Gurage languages|Gurage]] group. It is spoken in the mountains north of [[Cheha]] and [[Ezhana Wolene]] in Ethiopia. The language has two dialects, which are named after the first-person singular pronoun "I" they use: Ana uses ''əni''/''anä'', Adi uses ''adi''/''ädi'' (similar to the related language [[Soddo language|Soddo]]).
